<meta property="og:url" content="<%=root_url%>" />

<div class="container" id="content">
  <h1>StoryHooter</h1>


  <div class="panel panel-default">
    <div class="panel-heading">
      <a class="panel-title collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#panel-element-1">What is StoryHooter?</a>
    </div>
    <div id="panel-element-1" class="panel-collapse">
      <div class="panel-body">
        StoryHooter is a real-time user generated branching story inspired by games like <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Consequences_(game)">Consequences</a> and <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mad_Libs">Mad Libs</a>.
        <p>Below is a random story generated by people like you!</P>

        <%= render 'layouts/fancy_timeline_past' %>

      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="panel panel-default">
    <div class="panel-heading">
      <a class="panel-title collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#panel-element-2">How does it work?</a>
    </div>
    <div id="panel-element-2" class="panel-collapse collapse">
      <div class="panel-body">
        The story begins from a single line, ‘Once upon a time’. As people hear about it they can add to the story. Who you share your referral link with determines how the story continues.
        Because any number of people can add to the story at any given point the narrative quickly branches into an infinite number of endings.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="panel panel-default">
    <div class="panel-heading">
      <a class="panel-title collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#panel-element-3">How do I add to the story?</a>
    </div>
    <div id="panel-element-3" class="panel-collapse collapse">
      <div class="panel-body">
        You need to hear about it from someone!
        If someone sends you their referral link, you’ll be able to continue the story from where they left it.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="panel panel-default">
    <div class="panel-heading">
      <a class="panel-title collapsed" data-toggle="collapse" href="#panel-element-4">Who created this?</a>
    </div>
    <div id="panel-element-4" class="panel-collapse collapse">
      <div class="panel-body">
        <p>My day job is working as a software developer. I like to make random sites like this.</p>
        <p>You can contact me at <a href="mailto:hello.storyhooter@gmail.com">hello.storyhooter@gmail.com</a></p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

</div>
